raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.5' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tuneranger
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/tuneRanger_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/tuneRanger/tuneRanger_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a60cd0a05d0a95a7e4f3b836bfa34777d585d0df88332ea5e006ebe31046c7f5

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic

  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bbmisc >=1.11
    - r-dicekriging >=1.5.5
    - r-paramhelpers >=1.10
    - r-lhs >=0.14
    - r-lubridate >=1.6.0
    - r-mlr >=2.11
    - r-mlrmbo >=1.1.1
    - r-ranger >=0.8.0
    - r-smoof >=1.5.1

  run:
    - r-base
    - r-bbmisc >=1.11
    - r-dicekriging >=1.5.5
    - r-paramhelpers >=1.10
    - r-lhs >=0.14
    - r-lubridate >=1.6.0
    - r-mlr >=2.11
    - r-mlrmbo >=1.1.1
    - r-ranger >=0.8.0
    - r-smoof >=1.5.1

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('tuneRanger')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tuneRanger')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=tuneRanger
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Tuning random forest with one line. The package is mainly based on the packages 'ranger'
    and 'mlrMBO'.

  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - taylorreiter
